  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Outsource Manager",
  "description": "<p>Job Scope:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead accounting teams</li>\n  <li>Provide guidance to team members</li>\n  <li>Handle portfolio of clients, including assignment of jobs to teams and team members</li>\n  <li>Responsible for billings and debtor management for portfolio</li>\n  <li>Review work by accounting teams</li>\n  <li>Managing team workload to meet client deadline</li>\n</ul>\n<p>         -  Where possible or required, this would include negotiation with</p>\n<p>             the client on deadlines and corresponding fee adjustments</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Propose resolution steps for issues that may arise with clients</li>\n  <li>Report to director on the following</li>\n</ul>\n<p>         -  Issues that arise with clients</p>\n<p>         -  Anticipated issues that may arise (eg Deadline not able to be</p>\n<p>            met)</p>\n<p>         -  Time spent by teams on jobs</p>\n<p>Required experience:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 10 years of experience in outsource accounting and audit, of which a minimum of 4 years of experience in a supervisory/managerial role of 3 or more members</li>\n  <li>Proficient knowledge in Singapore Financial Reporting Standards</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge of Singapore payroll and taxation regulations</li>\n  <li>Knowledge and practical experience with various accounting systems</li>\n  <li>Member of a professional accountancy body (eg ISCA, ACCA, ICAEW, CPA Australia)</li>\n</ul>",
